headline.main: R.A.F. CHIEF SEES GERMANS IN PANIC; Coningham Says Supplies Are Being Flown to Libya to Bolster Nazi Force

lead_paragraph: ABOARD A BRITISH BOMBER, Over the Libyan Battlefield, Nov. 23 (AP) -- The Germans are rushing fighters, bombers, supplies of gasoline and anti-tank guns to North Africa by transport planes and gliders in a desperate effort to turn the tide of battle in Libya.
abstract: Germans rush supplies to Libya to bolster forces
